<h3>Week 3: Repurpose</h3>
<p>Week 3 turns the source article into derivative assets that live on different platforms.</p>
<ul>
<li>Convert the intro into a SlideShare or Notion lead magnet</li>
<li>Pull 5 quote graphics for Instagram and LinkedIn</li>
<li>Cut a 5-minute YouTube video from the full article</li>
<li>Submit to relevant industry roundups</li>
<li>Reply to comments on every previous post</li>
</ul>
<h3>Week 4: Compound</h3>
<p>Week 4 builds the internal infrastructure that makes the piece a long-term asset.</p>
<ul>
<li>Build 2 internal links from older posts back to this one</li>
<li>Update the original post with new comments, questions, or data</li>
<li>Review Google Search Console for ranking position</li>
<li>If ranking 5 to 15, refresh the piece for ranking jumps</li>
<li>Add to your monthly distribution performance report</li>
</ul>
<p>Run this cadence on every new piece. Within 90 days, you have 12 to 16 assets all compounding across 7 channels. That is what multi-channel content distribution actually looks like in practice.</p>
